   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/isolate_bypass_section"
                          class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Depending on the design and system
type, the system unit can be isolated without isolating the bypass.
The bypass section or system must be volt free before performing any
maintenance on the bypass stabilizer.</p>
      </div>
      <ol class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check the tension of the carbon rollers and brushes. The carbon
rollers and brushes need to apply sufficient pressure to the contact
surface.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the carbon rollers/brushes can rotate freely.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Worn carbon rollers and brushes must be replaced directly.<note class="- topic/note "> Worn carbon rollers and brushes might damage the winding, brush-holder
or contact surface.</note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Clean the contact surface from adhered dirt with a stiff brush.
The contact surface can also be cleaned with a contact cleaner lubricant. <note class="- topic/note ">Remember to remove the residue from the contact cleaner lubricant.</note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check if the brush guides and contacts are worn. Replace any
worn parts.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For transformers with spindle drivers:</b>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Grease the bearings and shafts.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Lubricate the bearing block.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Clean the contact surface with a contact cleaner lubricant.<note class="- topic/note ">Remember to remove the residue from the contact cleaner lubricant.</note>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
